<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="527" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,664,1807]" pageId="14" pageNumber="527">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,700,726]" pageId="14" pageNumber="527">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[329,588,700,727]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Glyphodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="527" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="formosanus">
<emphasis box="[329,588,700,727]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="527">Glyphodes formosanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished by the whitish forewing with the bar-shaped, slanted, dark brown antemedial line, the dark brown Y-shaped medial line and subtermen, and the whitish hindwing with dark brown V-shaped medial line with a large dot-shaped discal dot and the dark brown subtermen tinged with blackish scales. 
<taxonomicName box="[332,590,808,835]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Glyphodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="527" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="formosanus">
<emphasis box="[332,590,808,835]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="527">Glyphodes formosanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is externally similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Butler, 1879" authorityName="Butler" authorityYear="1879" box="[855,1103,808,835]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Margaronia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL,GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="527" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pryeri">
<emphasis box="[855,957,809,835]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="527">G. pryeri</emphasis>
Butler, 
<quantity box="[1047,1103,809,835]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.77266" pageId="14" pageNumber="527" unit="in" value="1879.0">1879</quantity>
</taxonomicName>
in wing pattern elements, but can be distinguished by the relatively thin antemedial band and Y-shaped medial line of the forewing, and the large discal dot and the blackish subterminal line of the hindwing.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="527" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,664,1807]" pageId="14" pageNumber="527">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,916,942]" pageId="14" pageNumber="527">Description.</emphasis>
Wingspan 
<quantity box="[475,559,917,943]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" pageId="14" pageNumber="527" unit="mm" value="23.0">23 mm</quantity>
. Antennae filiform; frons broad, yellowish white; maxillary palpi minute, tip whitish; labial palpi moderate in length, about twice to eye diameter, white, 2 
<superScript attach="left" box="[1018,1034,952,966]" fontSize="6" pageId="14" pageNumber="527">nd</superScript>
segment tinged with dark brownish scales. Body white. Forewing light white in ground color; basal part brownish thick slanted band; antemedial line band-shaped, brown with black border, posterior line dorsally extended and almost meet postmedial line; postmedian Y-shaped brown band, left arm relatively thick and with a medial white large dot, right arm tapered from costa to middle; central fascia with an anterior black dot; subtermen brownish with white band, bordered with a black dentate line; termen lined with black; fringe brownish hairs. Hindwing basally whitish, V-shaped brown band on dorsum and postmedian; antemedial with a brown stone-shaped dot; subtermen brownish with a dark brown or blackish thick line and tinged with dark brown scales on costa and dorsum; termen lined with black. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1180,1351,1204,1231]" pageId="14" pageNumber="527">Male genitalia</emphasis>
. Uncus long, basally and medially thin, distally expanded, apex claw-shaped; gnathos simple; juxta narrow strip-shaped; saccus rounded. Valva broad, distally expanded; costa basally sclerotized, bent, tapered, distally convex, hairy; fibula thin, waved process with a sharp tip; sacculus triangular, distally sharply pointed. Aedeagus stout, about 13 spinular cornuti in different sizes from long to short. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[750,947,1348,1375]" pageId="14" pageNumber="527">Female genitalia</emphasis>
. Papillae anales small; posterior apophyses thin, about the equal length of 8 
<superScript attach="left" box="[518,531,1384,1398]" fontSize="6" pageId="14" pageNumber="527">th</superScript>
segment; anterior apophyses basally thicker, gradually tapered distally, slightly longer than 8 
<superScript attach="left" box="[299,312,1420,1434]" fontSize="6" pageId="14" pageNumber="527">th</superScript>
segment; ostium bursae tube-shaped, ventrally thin, band-shaped sclerotization; ductus bursae long, posterior 1/2 strongly sclerotized, medially with ductus seminalis, anteriorly broader and twisted twice; corpus bursae small ovate, an irregular shape of signa patch with minute spicules.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="527" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,664,1807]" box="[199,729,1528,1555]" pageId="14" pageNumber="527">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1528,1554]" pageId="14" pageNumber="527">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[359,503,1528,1555]" name="South Korea" pageId="14" pageNumber="527">South Korea</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[514,599,1528,1554]" name="Taiwan" pageId="14" pageNumber="527">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[657,724,1529,1555]" name="Japan" pageId="14" pageNumber="527">Japan</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,664,1807]" pageId="14" pageNumber="527">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,396,1564,1590]" pageId="14" pageNumber="527">DNA barcoding.</emphasis>
One specimen from 
<collectingCountry box="[643,787,1564,1591]" name="South Korea" pageId="14" pageNumber="527">South Korea</collectingCountry>
(
<accessionNumber box="[805,932,1564,1591]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/OK501203" pageId="14" pageNumber="527">OK501203</accessionNumber>
) was sequenced, and the genetic difference between 
<taxonomicName box="[251,417,1601,1627]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Glyphodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="527" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="formosanus">
<emphasis box="[251,417,1601,1627]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="527">G. formosanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and its relative, 
<taxonomicName authority="Walker" authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1859" box="[602,812,1600,1627]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Glyphodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="527" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pyloalis">
<emphasis box="[602,725,1600,1627]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="527">G. pyloalis</emphasis>
Walker
</taxonomicName>
was 7.2%.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="527" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,664,1807]" pageId="14" pageNumber="527">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1637,1663]" pageId="14" pageNumber="527">Remarks.</emphasis>
The genus 
<emphasis box="[457,583,1636,1662]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="527">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Guenee" authorityYear="1854" box="[457,580,1636,1662]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Glyphodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="527" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Glyphodes</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
one of the species-rich groups of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1810" box="[1037,1163,1636,1662]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="527" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Crambidae</taxonomicName>
, comprises 156 species worldwide and the foodplants of the genus are primarily the latex-containing 
<taxonomicName box="[1013,1123,1673,1699]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Moraceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="14" pageNumber="527" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Moraceae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Mally et al., 2019)" baseAuthorityName="Mally" baseAuthorityYear="2019" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="14" pageNumber="527" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">
Apocynaceae (
<bibRefCitation author="Mally, R. &amp; Hayden, J. E. &amp; Neinhuis, C. &amp; Jordal, B. H. &amp; Nuss, M." pageId="14" pageNumber="527" pagination="141 - 204" refId="ref13812" refString="Mally, R., Hayden, J. E., Neinhuis, C., Jordal, B. H. &amp; Nuss, M. (2019) The phylogenetic systematics of Spilomelinae and Pyraustinae (Lepidoptera: Pyraloidea: Crambidae) inferred from DNA and morphology. Arthropod Systematics &amp; Phylogeny, Dresden, 77 (1), 141 - 204. https: // doi. org / 10.26049 / asp 77 - 1 - 2019 - 07" type="journal article" year="2019">
Mally 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="527">et al</emphasis>
., 2019
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. In 
<collectingCountry box="[304,371,1709,1735]" name="Japan" pageId="14" pageNumber="527">Japan</collectingCountry>
, many species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Guenee" authorityYear="1854" box="[569,689,1708,1734]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Glyphodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="527" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[569,689,1708,1734]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="527">Glyphodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(e.g., 
<taxonomicName authority="Leech" authorityName="Leech" box="[760,997,1708,1735]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Glyphodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="527" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bipunctalis">
<emphasis box="[760,918,1708,1735]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="527">G. bipunctalis</emphasis>
Leech
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Guenee" authorityName="Guenee" authorityYear="1854" box="[1008,1239,1708,1735]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Glyphodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="527" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bivitralis">
<emphasis box="[1008,1144,1708,1735]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="527">G. bivitralis</emphasis>
Guenée
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Butler" authorityName="Butler" authorityYear="1879" box="[1251,1432,1708,1735]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Margaronia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL,GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="527" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pryeri">
<emphasis box="[1251,1353,1709,1735]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="527">G. pryeri</emphasis>
Butler
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Walker" authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1859" box="[151,367,1744,1771]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Glyphodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="527" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pyloalis">
<emphasis box="[151,277,1744,1771]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="527">G. pyloalis</emphasis>
Walker
</taxonomicName>
) feed on the species of 
<taxonomicName box="[646,756,1745,1771]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Moraceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="14" pageNumber="527" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Moraceae</taxonomicName>
(http://www.jpmoth.org). In 
<collectingCountry box="[1090,1236,1744,1771]" name="South Korea" pageId="14" pageNumber="527">South Korea</collectingCountry>
, seven species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Guenee" authorityYear="1854" box="[151,271,1780,1806]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Glyphodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="527" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,271,1780,1806]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="527">Glyphodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are known.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
